<article id="er-article-body"><div id="mw-content-text" lang="en-GB" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><table id="toc" class="toc"><tbody><tr><td><div id="toctitle"><h2>Contents</h2></div><ul><li class="toclevel-1"><a href="#Terms_.26_Conditions_of_use_of_this_API"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">Terms &amp; Conditions of use of this API</span></a><ul><li class="toclevel-2"><a href="#General"><span class="tocnumber">1.1</span> <span class="toctext">General</span></a></li><li class="toclevel-2"><a href="#Fair_Usage_Policy"><span class="tocnumber">1.2</span> <span class="toctext">Fair Usage Policy</span></a></li><li class="toclevel-2"><a href="#Map_Tile_Server"><span class="tocnumber">1.3</span> <span class="toctext">Map Tile Server</span></a></li><li class="toclevel-2"><a href="#Third_Party_Data"><span class="tocnumber">1.4</span> <span class="toctext">Third Party Data</span></a></li></ul></li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table><h1> <span class="mw-headline" id="Terms_.26_Conditions_of_use_of_this_API">Terms &amp; Conditions of use of this API</span></h1><p>The following are the Terms &amp; Conditions for using the API's provided on the following sites: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://uktra.in/">uktra.in</a>, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://maidstoneweather.com/">maidstoneweather.com</a>, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://map.lu">map.lu</a>, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://area51.onl">area51.onl</a>, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://a51.li">a51.li</a>, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://iot.onl/">iot.onl</a> and <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://piweather.center/">piweather.center</a>.</p><h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="General">General</span></h2><ol><li> Any abuse of this <a href="//uktra.in/Api" title="Api">API</a> or of these Terms &amp; Conditions may result in your access being either throttled or blocked entirely.</li><li> You may use this <a href="//uktra.in/Api" title="Api">API</a> for Personal or Research purposes only. For any other use permission must be requested prior to use.</li><li> This <a href="//uktra.in/Api" title="Api">API</a> is provided as-is with no warranty on it's accuracy or availability.</li><li> Any <a href="//uktra.in/Api" title="Api">API</a>'s specification may be withdrawn at any time without any prior notice.</li><li> Most <a href="//uktra.in/Api" title="Api">API</a>'s are available without authentication, however where authentication is required then an API key will be required.<ol><li> The API key will be provided to you for your own use only.</li><li> You may not share that key with any third pary or make it public in any way.</li><li> Authenticated API's are strictly Server-Server only.</li></ol></li><li> All API calls are available via IPv4 and IPv6.</li><li> Although it's not necessary, if you use any of these API's please let me know so I know which API's are being actively used.</li><li> Currently only http access is available. https will be supported at a future date.</li></ol><h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Fair_Usage_Policy">Fair Usage Policy</span></h2><p>To ensure the safety of the system, a fair use policy is in place.</p><ol><li> Most API's are for Server to Server calls only. They should not be called from a user's browser. If an API is intended for use by a browser it will specify this within it's documentation.</li><li> Where possible cache responses to keep calls down</li><li> Do not call the API's too often. Ideally only call these no more than once every hour. For most of them the data is static or updated infrequently.</li><li> API calls that hold Real Time data will state this and will state how often you may call them.</li><li> If your application or site puts too great a load on our servers we may temporarily block you, throttle access or any other measure to ensure the other users are not affected.</li></ol><h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Map_Tile_Server">Map Tile Server</span></h2><ol><li> All maps are provided free of charge for personal use only.</li><li> Map data from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.openstreetmap.org/">OpenStreetMap</a> is licenced under the <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright">ODbL</a>. You must be aware of the details.</li><li> Attribution must be given when presenting any map tile. The full details are shown below.</li><li> Tiles may be cached and/or redistributed under the these terms.</li><li> <b>Absolutely no bulk-downloading, scraping, pre-downloading, pre-caching or anything similar is permitted under any circumstances.</b></li><li> Access to the tile server:<ol><li> When serving tiles to your own site you must use as the base URL either //tiles.map.lu/ or load balance them using a combination of the following hostnames: //a.tiles.map.lu/, //c.tiles.map.lu/ and //c.tiles.map.lu/.</li><li> You may not use any other url to get to the tile server.</li><li> If you want to brand the tile server to use your own domain name, e.g. tiles.uktra.in, this is possible. Please get in touch.</li></ol></li></ol><h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Third_Party_Data">Third Party Data</span></h2><ol><li> Some <a href="//uktra.in/Api" title="Api">API</a>'s use third party data under license. You must comply with those licenses if you use this data.</li><li> The following are the specifics for certain data. Attribution's here are in ADDITION to the global attribution listed above under General(2) above.</li><li> If you are using multiple sources then you must include all of them, although for some you may merge them - you can see some examples of this on various pages on this site.</li></ol><dl><dt> Open Street Map</dt><dd> Any images from our map server must be attributed with:</dd></dl><pre>Map imagery ©2012-2014 Peter Mount, data © OpenStreetMap contributors, CC-BY-SA.
